Commentary: OUT! OBSTRUCTING THE FIELD! A brain-fade moment for Mushfiqur Rahim as he becomes the first Bangladeshi batter to be out in this fashion. Kyle Jamieson lands this on a hard length and around off, Mushfiqur Rahim stays in his crease and bunts it out as the ball bounces off the ground and Rahim casually flicks the ball away using his hands. He did not need to do that as the ball was nowhere near the stumps. New Zealand players appeal and the umpires after a chat send it upstairs. The replay shows that he has deliberately handled the ball and he has to make that long walk back to the hut. New Zealand have been gifted a breakthrough here!
